  <sect2>
    <title>Installation</title>

    <para>
      Install the package by running the following commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>./configure --prefix=/usr \
            --with-gitconfig=/etc/gitconfig \
            --without-tcltk &amp;&amp;
make</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      If you have installed <xref linkend="asciidoc"/> and <xref
      linkend="xmlto"/> you can create the man pages:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>make man</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Alternatively, if you downloaded the man pages:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>tar xvf ../git-manpages-&git-version;.tar.xz</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Now, as the <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      If you created the man pages, install them as the <systemitem
      class="username">root</systemitem> user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install-man</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Alternatively, if you downloaded the man pages:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>for dir in man? ; do cp -v $dir/* /usr/share/man/$dir ; done</userinput></screen>

    <sect3>
      <title>Command Explanations</title>

      <para>
        <parameter>--with-gitconfig=/etc/gitconfig</parameter>: This sets
        <filename>/etc/gitconfig</filename> as the file that stores the default,
        system wide, Git settings.
      </para>

      <para>
        <parameter>--without-tcltk</parameter>: This switch disables Tcl/Tk GUI
        as it breaks the build if gettext-tiny is installed.
      </para>

      <para>
        <option>--without-python</option>: Use this switch if Python is not
        installed.
      </para>

      <para>
        <option>--with-libpcre</option>: Use this switch if PCRE is installed.
      </para>

    </sect3>

  </sect2>

